The R.P.D. was the first machine gun designed to fire the 7.62x39mm cartridge.

The R.P.D. platform has been issued by many countries including the Soviet Union, China, Egypt and former Eastern Bloc countries.

The R.P.D. was also used by the U.S. SOF in Vietnam.

DSA has modernized this battlefield benchmark with features such as a newly designed 7075T6 alloy lower and proprietary rail handguard.

In addition, the DSA barrel is fluted and shortened.

This reduces weight and helps keep the barrel cool.

A very effective, proven design flashhider has also been added.

These features have reduced the R.P.D. weight by almost 2 pounds.

title: For Sale:  SIG P225 (not P6) with 5 mags, case, 1999 production
postcontent:
SIG-Sauer P225

This is a commercial P-225, not a police surplus P6.

    SIG P225 9mm pistol
    original factory hard case
    5 factory magazines
    - the 2 magazines that came with the gun are marked "SIG SAUER"
    - the 3 extra magazines are marked "P6 9mm", and were purchased from CDNN
    - new factory magazines $37 from CDNN and  $40 from Top Gun Supply  (when available)

This gun was manufactured in 1999 in Germany, and I bought it in 2002.  I only shot this once or twice.

After the terrorist attack at the Munich Olympics in 1972, the West German police decided to standardize on the 9mm cartridge for their service pistols.  This was an era when .32 ACP and .380 ACP handguns were commonly issued in Europe.  The SIG-Sauer P225 was adopted by the West German police as the P6.  The other two pistols adopted were the Walther P5 and the Heckler & Koch P7.  When the German police adopted the P8 (a variant of the H&K USP) in the late 1990s, along with the Walther P99, surplus P5, P6, and P7 pistols became available on the American market around 2004 - 2005.    This is not one of those surplus German police guns, and there are some minor differences between the two. Other sellers often conflate the commercial P225 and surplus P6 pistols; either knowingly or honestly out of ignorance.

Armslist only allows the posting of three photos.  More photos are available upon request.

I can meet you at an FFL dealer of your choice to conduct transfer in accordance with stupid state laws.  Buyer is responsible for FFL and CBI fees.

title: For Sale:  WW2 8MM Czech VZ24 Mauser (arsenal rebuild)

In fact, this rifle was probably captured from the Germans during WW2 by the Yugoslovians.

BCG is a PSA premium HPT/MPI full auto with a PSA charging handle.  It has a Magpul MOE stock, Magpul BUIS and Magpul ASAP sling attachment point. 120 Federal XM855 62gr

2 PMAG GEN M3

1 Lancer 20rd

Not pictured but included will be a Midway tactical case (OD) and a Tapco Intrafuse AR tool. *UPDATE* Seems I could only post a single photo.  Please let me know if you want photos of anything.

For everything above I am asking $800.  I am very motivated to get this sold.  Feel free to make a reasonable offer.  I am selling this all to help fund a trip.  An opportunity came up I did not expect, this is all just sitting around and should have a good home.

NV residents only, and we will do a bill of sale.

I may consider a partial trade for the entire package only.  Something in 9mm, 45, 357 or 38 may interest me.  There will need to be cash on your side though.  So do not be offended if I am picky about any sort of trade.  Cash is king right now, but feel free to ask.

As promised here is another once in a lifetime opportunity to own something that is so rare! A brand new, in the box, PPK (not PPK/S), Manufactured in Germany and Proofed in Germany, No IMPORT MARKS, with all original paperwork, extra magazine, matching target, cleaning tool, rare matching black box in .380 auto/9 mm Kurz. I have a limited number of these beautiful, highly polished, brand new, PPK with NO IMPORT MARKS and some with consecutive serial numbers (please contact me). These PPK's have been stored in a warehouse by the importer for years, heavily oiled (as noted in the picture). All “German” PPK guns after WWII and until 1986 have been manufactured in France, not Germany, and proofed in Germany so they were allowed to say “Made in Germany” by European regulations. These are manufactured in ULM, Germany and Proofed in ULM, Germany. This PPK is absolutely beautiful, museum quality, with no imperfections and an amazing high polish deep bluing that only the Germans are capable of. In fact, I was hesitant to take it out of the wrapping and take the pictures. This is it Collectors. Last chance… These are the only Brand New German made PPK's in the USA that I know of that are made in Germany after the war and offered to the public.

title: For Sale/Trade:  WTT/WTS: S&W Model 41 7" Target .22lr Pistol
postcontent:
Hi I have for sale a S&W Model 41 7" Target .22lr Pistol.
THESE DONT COME UP FOR SALE OR TRADE VERY OFTEN SO THEY ARE WHAT I SOULD SAY IS RARE.
It is used and dates to late 1978 according to S&W serial #. 
It has a rich royal blue finish with polished sides and matte finish on the top.
As you can see in the pictures it does have a few issues to the finish.
First is the left side of slide and barrel have some scratches in it.
Second would be the front of slide and barrel have surface rust on it.
Third would be the bottom left side of grip has a nicks in it where the wood chipped off. THIS IS MORE OF A SHOOTER THAN A COLLECTABLE BUT COULD BE BOTH IF TAKEN TO A GUNSMITH.

With that being said these go for $1200-1300 NEW and $900-1200 used from what I could find on line. 

The grips can be had on S&W sight for $67. Easy fix. 
As far as the slight surface rust you could use some oil and 0000 steel wool and GENTLY brush forward to get the rust off. There are U-tube videos of it.
The scratches can be sanded out by a gunsmith and re-blued. 
I would do this but I just don't have the time to deal with it. 

 I just put 50 rounds through it at Shooters World last night and it ran flawlessly.

Now for the price: I'm asking $700 OBO or EQUAL value trade for other firearms. NO SHOTGUNS OR RIFLES please. 

Shoot me your offers. The worst I can say is NO THANKS.
If you have a trade please let me know: make, model, finish and what goes with it and what your asking. 
I can do a partial trade also.


You can contact me through the ad or through TEXT any time and I will get back with you a.s.a.p.

 Thanks
 JD

I HAVE MORE PICTURES UPON REQUEST

title: For Sale:  S&W M&P 45, LNIB…Case, 3 Grip Sizes, 3 Hi Cap Mags
postcontent: S&W M&P 45, LNIB… Case, 3 Grip Sizes, 3 Hi Capacity Mags… Original Police Issue but hardly used… Like New!!! The M&P 45 is just what it sounds like; it’s the .45 ACP version of the M&P series of handguns. It shares the same injection-molded polymer frame and black oxide forged stainless steel slide. It also comes with 3 sizes of palm swell (small, medium, large) for those of all hand sizes. The M&P 45 also comes with 3­dot fixed sights and a reversible magazine release button, plus 3 High Capacity Mags… The M&P 45 is an excellent choice as a combat pistol for many reasons. The M&P 45 is a double stack 45, meaning that its magazine holds 10 rounds. That’s two more than the modern 1911. Like the Glock and XD, the M&P mag well is plenty wide for quick and positive magazine changes. The M&P 45 sports forward and rear cocking serrations that aid in press checking the gun to see if it’s loaded and getting it back into battery after a slide lock reload.
